com.github.arachnidium.model.abstractions

Class ModelObject<S extends Handle>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.arachnidium.model.abstractions.ModelObject<S>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - It means that objects can be stationed on browser window or mobile application screen.
    If there is
    <S extends Handle> or
    * <Handle> it means that both BrowserWindow and MobileScreen are possible. It is good for situations when interaction with UI of browser client and the perfectly similar mobile client has to be automated.

    If it needs to be bounded by only one Handle subclass (BrowserWindow or MobileScreen) then
    - <BrowserWindow> - only browser windows

    or

    - <MobileScreen> - only mobile screens
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDestroyable, IDecomposable, org.openqa.selenium.internal.WrapsDriver
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Application, FunctionalPart

    public abstract class ModelObject<S extends Handle>
extends Object
implements IDestroyable, IDecomposable, org.openqa.selenium.internal.WrapsDriver
    This is a basic abstraction which describes objects are used for modeling application.
